    <text>
        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>53 Anderson St<lb/>
                Montreal&#44; Aug. 28. 1885.<lb/></p>
                
            <p>Rev. S. Morais<lb/>
                Philadelphia Pa.<lb/></p>
            <p>My dear Sir&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>Knowing your influence on&#44; and<lb/> among the Jewish communities of the United<lb/> States&#44; I take the liberty in addressing this note<lb/> to you&#44; and the courtesy usually extended to<lb/> strangers&#44; I hope you will not refuse me&#44; but<lb/> interest yourself in my behalf as much as<lb/> circumstances may permit.<lb/></p>
            <p>In England I held the office of<lb/> Reader&#44; teacher etc. under the jurisdiction<lb/> of the Rev. Dr. Adler&#44; Chief Rabbi&#44; London&#44;<lb/> during six years&#44; upon his recommendation and<lb/> that of the late Dr Artom&#44; I was elected teacher<lb/> by the Portuguese Congregation in this City ten<lb/> years ago&#44; and have remained in its employ<lb/> ever since&#44; now however&#44; necessity will <sic>compell</sic><lb/>me to change places&#59; I shall esteem it an ever&#45;<lb/></p>
            
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>lasting favor if you will kindly offer me<lb/> your advice&#59; and if possible aid me in obtain&#45;<lb/>ing another situation.<lb/></p>
            <p>I respectfully enclose copies of creden&#45;<lb/>tials for your kind inspection.<lb/></p>
            <p>Should this be favorably received&#44;<lb/>surely you would always find me worthy of<lb/> your consideration.<lb/></p>
            <p>I am&#44;<lb/>
                Rev. Sir&#44;<lb/>
                Yours very respectfully&#44;<lb/>
                A. Jacoby<lb/></p>	
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>Copies<lb/></p>
            <p>1.Resolved&#58; that the thanks of the Con&#45;<lb/>gregation be given Mr Jacoby for the<lb/> very efficient and satisfactory manner<lb/> in which he has conducted the Hebrew<lb/> teaching of the scholars attached to<lb/> the Jewish School of this Corporation.<lb/></p>
            <p>1.	A true copy from the minutes<lb/>
                J. Samuel&#44;<lb/>
                Secretary&#44;<lb/>
                Portuguese Congregation.<lb/></p>
            <p>2. Montreal 14<hi rend="sup">th</hi> May&#44; 1884.<lb/></p>
            <p>This is to certify that I have known<lb/> Mr. Aaron Jacoby for a number of years<lb/> past&#44; intimately&#44; and also officially&#44;<lb/> in my capacity of Secretary of the Board<lb/> of School Commissioners and would say<lb/> that I consider him to be an efficient<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="4"/>
            <p>Teacher and one who has proved himself<lb/> to be a most useful member of our Congregation&#59;<lb/> as an assistant to the minister&#44; and in other<lb/>ways&#44; and we shall all deeply regret<lb/> if he is taken away from us even to be<lb/> in a sphere of more extended useful&#45;<lb/>ness than he can possibly be here&#44;<lb/> in our small congregation.<lb/></p>
            <p>He will surely have with him&#44;<lb/>wherever he goes&#44; the best wishes of all<lb/> here&#44; for he is very popular and liked<lb/> by all&#44; is very gentlemanly&#44; and upright<lb/> in character and thoroughly conversant<lb/> with whatsoever duties he may under&#45;<lb/>take&#44; and above all is sound in his religious doctrine.<lb/></p>
            <p>Emil A. Hart.<lb/></p>
            <p>3.
                527 Recollet St.<lb/></p>
            <p>Montreal&#44; 3 Aug. 1885.<lb/>
                Mr. A. Jacoby has been in Montreal<lb/> for the last ten years during which<lb/></p> 
                
                <pb n="5"/>
            <p>time he has been teaching<lb/> Hebrew and German&#44; we can<lb/> highly recommend him as a <lb/>competent teacher&#44; and one who<lb/> takes great interest in his pupils&#44;<lb/> he was recommended to us by<lb/> Rev. Dr. Adler Chief Rabbi of<lb/> England.<lb/></p>
            <p>&#40;Signed&#41; Hyman Moss&#44;<lb/>
                John E. Moss.<lb/></p>
            <p>4.</p>
            <p>I hereby certify that Mr Jacoby<lb/> has filled the position of Hebrew<lb/> teacher in my congregation. During that<lb/> <del>that</del> time he has discharged his duties<lb/> in the most thorough and faithful<lb/> manner and to the entire satisfaction<lb/> of the congregation. He has shown<lb/> excellent qualification for his<lb/> calling and has succeeded in im&#45;<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="6"/>
            <p>parting knowledge where many less<lb/> able and less persevering would<lb/> have failed.<lb/></p>
            <p>Meldola de Sola&#44;<lb/>
                Minister&#44;<lb/>
                K.K. Shearith Israel<lb/>
                Montreal.<lb/>
                Aug. 20. 1885.<lb/></p>
